loration of childhood as a concept, in the process engaging with a range of contemporary issues that shape our ideas of childhood as an ideal and a lived experience. The diverse nature of childhood is a key theme, explored here from different research perspectives and academic traditions. A range of anthropological, developmental and sociocultural approaches are also discussed. This volume is the first in a series of four books, written by experts in the field, which provides an introduction to childhood degree programmes and related modules. The series features international case studies, examples and readings to supplement the chapters, and is illustrated in full colour. Other books in the series are: · Children and young people's cultural worlds · Childhoods in context · Local childhoods, global issues  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aChild development. 0aChildren. 0aElectronic books. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh1 aBrockliss, Laurence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGallacher, Lesley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHammersley, Martyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKehily, Mary Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKehily, Mary Jane, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMontgomery, Heather, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWoodhead, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144730580440uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447342953?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447342953423Coveruhttps://